                    Who We Are:

InGenius Prep was founded in 2013 by law students at Harvard and Yale. In that time, the company has grown to a team of more than 190 full-time employees, 600 part-time employees, as well as offices in the U.S., Canada, China, amongst other countries. 



What We Do: 

You are the engine that keeps our technical delivery pipeline moving, ensuring maintenance intake is recorded and moves visibly and reliably from scope to build to QA through the release. Your responsibilities include:

Maintain the delivery board, tracking milestones, dependencies, and risks;

Act as the primary point of contact for internal staff and our vendor (Folio3) to follow up on blockers and minimize project slippage;

Handle day-to-day vendor execution coordination and QA as needed;

Organize reviews, QA cycles, and release readiness;

Maintain documentation for systems, ownership, and "what’s in flight";

Manage ticket recording for maintenance and feature requests on the InGenius end.



You’ll Be a Good Fit If You Have

We are looking for someone strong in execution, follow-through, and organization, rather than a senior product leader or engineer. You are a good fit if you have:

Demonstrated experience in program coordination, project management, or operations;

The ability to learn quickly in ambiguous environments;

Excellent communication skills and the ability to surface risks early;

A proven track record of holding stakeholders accountable to deadlines to push work to completion.

Experience working with tools such as Jira, project boards, or similar workflow tracking systems is preferred.



Benefits:

InGenius Prep offers employees a competitive salary along with paid time off, parental leave, remote work flexibility, professional development and a fun, collaborative work environment.



What We Believe:

InGenius Prep is an equal opportunity employer, and all qualified candidates will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability or veteran status.
